# `docs/tmp/` — opt-in working notes

**Default for every task: SKIP `docs/tmp/` entirely** — do not read `.active`, do not create files here, do not load this rule unless the conditions below are met.

## When this rule applies

| Condition | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| User message **names `docs/tmp`** (e.g. „użyj docs/tmp dla security”, „od etapu 1 pracuj z docs/tmp/security”) | **Activate** — follow [Activation](#activation) below |
| `docs/tmp/.active` exists **and** the current task clearly continues that feature (same epic/phase) | **Continue** — follow [Continuation](#continuation) below |
| Neither | **SKIP** — ignore this folder |

**Never activate** because work „seems complex”. You may **propose** once via `AskQuestion` (Yes/No); only activate after explicit Yes or user naming `docs/tmp`.

## Activation (user named `docs/tmp`)

1. Read this rule (you are here).
2. Resolve **feature** from user message (kebab-case, e.g. `security`). Ask if ambiguous.
3. In **this repo**, write `docs/tmp/.active` — **one line**, feature name only (e.g. `security`).
4. Create or open `docs/tmp/<feature>/STATUS.md` — use template in [`docs/tmp/README.md`](../../docs/tmp/README.md).
5. Cross-repo: if both repos are open and the feature spans both, repeat steps 3–4 in the other repo with the **same** feature name.

## Continuation (`.active` already set)

1. Read `docs/tmp/.active` (one line → feature name).
2. Read `docs/tmp/<feature>/STATUS.md` **before** editing code.
3. Do **not** create a new `.active` or subfolder without user naming `docs/tmp` again (switching features requires new activation).

## While active — agent duties

**Read order:** permanent doc for the domain (e.g. `docs/security.md`) → `STATUS.md` → other files in subfolder only if `STATUS.md` links them. **On conflict, permanent docs win** — fix or trim stale tmp.

**Maintain `STATUS.md`:** update `Last updated`, `Current focus`, `Done`, and **`Next agent action`** (imperative, concrete steps) at end of each session before handing off.

**Do not duplicate** rollout plans, `architecture.md`, or large specs — delta and decisions only.

## Teardown (user says feature done / close docs/tmp / delete tmp)

1. Promote durable facts to the correct permanent doc.
2. Delete `docs/tmp/<feature>/` and `docs/tmp/.active`.
3. Cross-repo: tear down in both repos if both were active.

## Proposal (optional, once per task)

If complexity clearly benefits from tmp **and** user has not named `docs/tmp`:

Use `AskQuestion`: „Czy włączyć docs/tmp/<proposed-feature> na handoff między sesjami?” — Yes/No. **No → do not mention tmp again this session** unless user brings it up.
